Image 75 of 75 Thousands expected at Foam Wonderland San Antonio 2015 this weekend 1 / 75 Back to Gallery A party billed as "the ultimate" experience has already covered venues in cities like Panama City and Austin in foam and will do the same at San Antonio's Freeman Coliseum Expo Hall on Saturday.
Foam Wonderland is an “interactive, safe” experience, owner of CrowdSurf Concerts, the event’s organizer, Au Hua said Wednesday.
“Our goal is to create a storm-like atmosphere as if our attendees are dancing in a rainstorm,” he said.
DJs like R3hab, Brillz and Zaxx are lined up to create the rainstorm’s soundtrack and have crowds dancing 6 p.m. to midnight.
As the name implies, there will be suds everywhere.
RELATED: mySpy: Tens of thousands hit opening weekend of ACL fest
“The most exciting element is obviously the foam,” Hua said. “You will get wet. “
Thousands of Instagram posts from past events prove what Hua said is true. Foam beards, wet hair and festival-worthy costumes fill the social network under the #FoamWonderland hashtag, uniting electronic dance music fans across the country who have survived the sudsy storm.
Although a large majority of the dancing crowd are EDM fans, Hua said his event is welcome to all.
“It’s an event for everyone, not just dance music lovers,” he said.
Organizers expect several thousand people to be at this weekend’s event, according to the website.
To be one of the thousands, San Antonians can purchase their way in by visiting Loop1Tickets.com . General admission tickets are $30. For an additional $15 party goers can get VIP access with “Express Entry” and free Foam Wonderland merchandise, according to the ticket site.
Click through the gallery above to see what you can expect to experience at the Foam Wonderland San Antonio 2015.
